content: Do not BUY this game, my twins finished it in 1 sitting, maybe 25-30 minutes. Google play would not refund because it "isnt in policy" just get Dulingo for free and have the kids do basic lessons over and over. :-)
Way too little content, which is a shame because it's a great program otherwise!
Its very short. Not a lot of content.
Can't hear anything volume is so low
My son finished this game way too quickly. For this price, there should be way more cities to unlock. Not happy.

It was a nice app but it barely provided any lessons. Not worth paying 
money for.
My daughter is 5 and loved this. I love all the games. But she finished the whole thing in one sitting. I thought it would unlock another map but there is no more than those 4 places on the map.
My 4 and 5 year old love it.

I found Gus on the Go to be very intuitive, clear and fun for kids and even adults. This is an excellent way to pick up/brush up on basic vocabulary words and to learn the correct pronunciation. I highly recommend and I'm looking forward to seeing more languages (especially Japanese!).
Cute app that provides a great learning experience while being fun for kids. I found myself using it to relearn spanish 101 basic vocab. Looking forward to meeting Gus in a few other countries!

I have a 4 year old niece who quickly picked up how to go through the learning sections and then loved playing the mini games. They were all easy for her to figure out and she loved the little cheer that she got when she finished a game. It's a great way to get kids familiar with basic words.
